# DVC Configuration for Yandex Cloud Object Storage
# ==================================================
#
# This project uses DVC with Yandex Cloud S3-compatible storage.
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# -------------------
#
# 1. Create a Yandex Cloud bucket:
#    https://console.cloud.yandex.ru/folders/<folder-id>/storage
#
# 2. Get credentials:
#    - Access Key ID
#    - Secret Access Key
#    - Bucket name
#
# 3. Configure DVC (run these commands):
#
#    # Initialize DVC
#    dvc init
#
#    # Add Yandex Cloud remote (replace with your values)
#    dvc remote add -d storage s3://<your-bucket-name>/dvc-storage
#
#    # Configure S3 endpoint for Yandex Cloud
#    dvc remote modify storage endpointurl https://storage.yandexcloud.net
#
#    # Set credentials (or use environment variables)
#    dvc remote modify storage access_key_id <your-access-key>
#    dvc remote modify storage secret_access_key <your-secret-key>
#
# 4. Commit DVC configuration:
#    git add .dvc/config
#    git commit -m "feat: initialize DVC with Yandex Cloud storage"
#
# 5. Add data directories:
#    dvc add data/raw
#    dvc add data/processed
#
# 6. Push to remote:
#    dvc push
#
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (alternative to storing credentials in config):
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID     - Your Yandex Cloud access key
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY - Your Yandex Cloud secret key
#
# USAGE EXAMPLES:
# ---------------
# dvc add data/raw/audio           # Track new data
# dvc push                         # Upload to Yandex Cloud
# dvc pull                         # Download from Yandex Cloud
# dvc status                       # Check data status
# dvc gc                           # Garbage collect unused data
